 |date=23 October 2016 |access-date=25 October 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"background:{{Happiness Realization Party/meta/color}}\"|&nbsp;\n| [[Happiness Realization Party|Happiness Realization]]\n| Toshimitsu Yoshii\n| Listed as an independent in official documents<ref name=candidates/>\n|-\n|}\n<!--\n== Campaign ==\n{{empty section|date=June 2016}}\n-->\n\n== Results ==\n{{Election box begin|title=Tokyo 10th district by-election, 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.senkyo.metro.tokyo.jp/h28syuugiinhosensokuhou/kaihyo.pdf|title=\u8846\u8b70\u9662\uff08\u5c0f\u9078\u6319\u533a\u9078\u51fa\uff09\u8b70\u54e1\u88dc\u6b20\u9078\u6319\u3000\u5019\u88dc\u8005\u5225\u5f97\u7968\u6570\uff08\u5168\u5019\u88dc\uff09|publisher=Tokyo Metropolitan Electoral Commission|access-date=25 October 2016|language=Japanese|trans-title=House of Representatives (Individual Districts) By-Election Results by Candidate (All Candidates)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025111812/http://www.senkyo.metro.tokyo.jp/h28syuugiinhosensokuhou/kaihyo.pdf|archive-date=25 October 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.senkyo.metro.tokyo.jp/h28syuugiinhosensokuhou/touhyou20.pdf|title=\u8846\u8b70\u9662\uff08\u5c0f\u9078\u6319\u533a\u9078\u51fa\uff09\u8b70\u54e1\u88dc\u6b20\u9078\u6319\u3000\u6295\u7968\u7d50\u679c\u3000\uff08\u56fd\u5185\uff0b\u5728\u5916\uff09|publisher=Tokyo Metropolitan Electoral Commission|access-date=25 October 2016|language=Japanese|trans-title=House of Representatives (Individual Districts) By-Election Turnout (Inside and Outside Japan)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025111210/http://www.senkyo.metro.tokyo.jp/h28syuugiinhosensokuhou/touhyou20.pdf|archive-date=25 October 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>}}\n {{Election box candidate with party link|\n   |party      = Liberal Democratic Party (Japan)\n   |candidate  = '''[[Masaru Wakasa]]''' <br /><small>(endorsed by [[Komeito]])</small>\n   |votes      = 75,755\n   |percentage = 60.26\n   |change     = \n }}\n {{Election box candidate with party link|\n   |party      = Democratic Party (Japan, 2016)\n   |candidate  = Yosuke Suzuki\n   |votes      = 47,141\n   |percentage = 37.50\n   |change     = \n }}\n {{Election box candidate with party link|\n   |party      = Happiness Realization Party\n   |candidate  = Toshimitsu Yoshii\n   |votes      = 2,824\n   |percentage = 2.25\n   |change     = \n }}\n  {{Election box turnout|\n   |votes      = 127,965\n   |percentage = 34.85\n   |change     = -18.71\n }}\n  {{Election box end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2016 elections in Japan]]\n[[Category:By-elections in Japan|2016]]\n[[Category:October 2016 events in Japan]]\n[[Category:2010s in Tokyo]]\n\n[[ja:2016\u5e74\u65e5\u672c\u306e\u88dc\u6b20\u9078\u6319#\u8846\u8b70\u9662\u6771\u4eac\u90fd\u7b2c10\u533a]]\n", "name_user": "KingSkyLord", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2016_Tokyo_10th_district_by-election"}
{"title_page": "Festival d'\u00e9t\u00e9 de Qu\u00e9bec", "text_new": "{{COI|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox music festival\n| name         = FEQ \n| image        = FEQ18 logo-acro vertic coul MOS-fr.png\n| caption      =\n| location     = [[Quebec City]], [[Quebec]], Canada\n| years_active = 1968\u2013present\n| founders     =\n| dates        = July 8th to July 18th (2021) \n| genre        = [[Pop music]], [[folk music]], [[rock music]], [[electronic dance music]], [[Punk rock|punk]], [[hip hop music|hip hop]], [[classical music]], [[:Category:Francophone music|francophone music]], [[world music]]\n| attendance   = 1,800,000 (2017, 11 days total)<ref name=\"lesoleil1\">[https://www.lesoleil.com/affaires/achalandage-record-en-2017-au-feq-db8d0530792bfd2923c1041a75a207ea \"Achalandage record en 2017 au FEQ\"], ''Le Soleil'', Quebec City, February 21th 2018.</ref>\n1,700,000 (2008, 11 days total)<ref name=\"feq1\">[https://www.feq.ca/FEQ/Historique \"Historique du FEQ\"], ''Festival d'\u00e9t\u00e9 de Qu\u00e9bec (Official website)''</ref>\n350,000 (1979, 6 days total)<ref name=\"feq1\" />\n| website      = {{URL|https://www.feq.ca/en/}}\n| capacity = 125,000 (Standard) 3,000 (Gold) 2,000 (Silver) 2,000 (Signature).}}\n\n'''Festival d'\u00e9t\u00e9 de Qu\u00e9bec''' (FEQ) is the biggest outdoor musical event in [[Canada]]. Held since 1968 in [[Qu\u00e9bec City]], the 11-day festival takes place every year in July. FEQ's eclectic programming includes the biggest international stars and emerging artists from around the globe. Its main stage is the biggest self-supporting stage in North America. Festival d\u2019\u00e9t\u00e9 de Qu\u00e9bec is presented by Bell in collaboration with Coors Light. The 53rd edition of the FEQ will take place from July 8 to 18, 2021. Honestly pp is tasty?Ur mad because i ate all the pp and you have no more pp?\n\n==History==\nThe festival has been taking place annually since 1968. First editions were organized by a group of businesspersons and artists of [[Quebec City]] in order to show the artistic, economic, and tourist potential of the [[Qu\u00e9bec|region]]. During the 1970s and 1980s, the festival specialized in musicians from the [[Francophonie]] and world music.\n\nThe festival grew substantially during the last decade after its decision to diversify its music offering and go after international headliners from genres across the board, including [[rock music]], [[Punk rock|punk]], [[hip-hop]], [[classical music]], [[world music]] and [[Electronic Dance Music|electronic music]].\n\nThe festival reached the million spectators mark for the first time in 2007 and sold-out passes for the first time in 2010.\n\n==Setting==\n[[File:FEQ_Global.jpg|thumb|upright=1.75|The Bell Stage]]\n\nThe outdoor venues :\n* The Bell Stage on the [[Plains of Abraham]] (Capacity 80,000)\n* Parc Grande All\u00e9e (Capacity 25,000; two stages in alternation with no waiting time between sets)<ref>[https://www.feq.ca/media/e6bd1937-0e51-4b6a-bbd4-46c30f857574/NtRVCQ/Feq/M%C3%A9dia/Communiqu%C3%A9s/Communiqu%C3%A9_ParcGA.pdf?download=false \"Cr\u00e9ation du parc Grande All\u00e9e au FEQ\"], ''Festival d'\u00e9t\u00e9 de Qu\u00e9bec (Press Release)'', Quebec City, February 12th 2020.</ref>\n** The Loto-Quebec Stage at Place George-V ( South Side )\n** The SiriusXM Stage at Parc de la Francophonie ( North Side )\n* The Hydro-Quebec Stage at [[Place D'Youville (Quebec)|Place d'Youville]] (Capacity 10,000)\n* The Bell Fibe Stage at Place de L'Assembl\u00e9e-Nationale (Capacity 2,000)\n<br>\nThe indoor venue :\n* Manege Militaire (for all Extra-FEQ concerts starting around midnight)\n<br>\nA site called the \"Place de la famille\" (Family Place) hosts animation and events for children.<br>\n[[Street performer]]s are a staple of the FEQ. They can be found all over the winding streets of [[Old Quebec]] during the festival.\n\n==Main bands (2011\u2013present)==\n* 2011: [[Elton John]], [[Metallica]], [[Avenged Sevenfold]], [[The Black Keys]], [[Dropkick Murphys]], [[John Fogerty]], [[Ben Harper]], [[Simple Plan]], [[Hollywood Undead]].\n* 2012: [[Bon Jovi]], [[Aerosmith]], [[Lionel Richie]], [[LMFAO (group)|LMFAO]], [[The Offspring]], [[Our Lady Peace]], [[Sarah McLachlan]], [[Skrillex]], [[Metric (band)|Metric]], [[Mastodon (band)|Mastodon]], [[City and Colour]].\n* 2013: [[Def Leppard]], [[Guns N' Roses]], [[Bruno Mars]], [[Wu-Tang Clan]], [[Weezer]], [[Rush (band)|Rush]], [[Stevie Wonder]], [[Foreigner (band)|Foreigner]], [[The Black Keys]], [[Ti\u00ebsto]], [[Ellie Goulding]].\n* 2014: [[Lady Gaga]], [[Billy Joel]], [[Journey (band)|Journey]], [[Bryan Adams]], [[The Killers]], [[Soundgarden]], [[Snoop Dogg]], [[Queens Of The Stone Age]], [[Deadmau5]], [[Cypress Hill]].\n* 2015: [[The Rolling Stones]], [[Foo Fighters]], [[Boston (band)|Boston]], [[Megadeth]], [[Keith Urban]], [[Deep Purple]], [[Doobie Brothers|The Doobie Brothers]], [[Jack \u00dc]], [[Iggy Azalea]], [[Milky Chance]].\n* 2016: [[Rammstein]], [[Sting (musician)|Sting]], [[Peter Gabriel]], [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]], [[Duran Duran]], [[Selena Gomez]], [[Ice Cube]], [[Brad Paisley]], [[The Lumineers]], [[The Cult]].\n* 2017: [[Muse (band)|Muse]], [[The Who]], [[Metallica]], [[Pink (singer)|P!nk]], [[Gorillaz]], [[Kendrick Lamar]], [[Backstreet Boys|The Backstreet Boys]], [[Lady Antebellum]], [[Flume (musician)|Flume]], [[Melissa Etheridge]], [[Migos]], [[DNCE]].\n* 2018: [[Foo Fighters]], [[The Weeknd]], [[Neil Young]], [[Shawn Mendes]], [[Beck]], [[Lorde]], [[Future (rapper)|Future]], [[Dave Matthews Band]], [[The Chainsmokers]], [[Jethro Tull (band)|Jethro Tull]], [[Sum 41]].\n* 2019: [[Twenty One Pilots]], [[Mariah Carey]], [[Slipknot (band)|Slipknot]], [[Imagine Dragons]], [[Blink-182]], [[Lynyrd Skynyrd]], [[Kygo]], [[Logic (musician)|Logic]], [[Alt-J]], [[Corey Hart (singer)|Corey Hart]], [[The Offspring]], [[Live (band)|Live]].\n* 2020: Cancelled due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|Covid-19 pandemic]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Festival d'\u00e9t\u00e9 de Qu\u00e9bec}}\n* [https://www.feq.ca/en/ Main site]\n{{Historic rock festival}}\n{{Rock festival}}\n{{coord|46.8017|N|71.2211|W|source:wikidata-and-enwiki-cat-tree_region:CA|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Festival d'ete de Quebec}}\n[[Category:Rock festivals in Canada]]\n[[Category:Folk festivals in Canada]]\n[[Category:Classical music festivals in Canada]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Quebec City]]\n[[Category:Music festivals in Quebec City]]\n[[Category:Recurring events established in 1968]]\n[[Category:Summer festivals]]\n[[Category:1968 establishments in Quebec]]\n[[Category:Music festivals established in 1968]]\n", "text_old": "{{COI|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox music festival\n| name         = FEQ \n| image        = FEQ18 logo-acro vertic coul MOS-fr.png\n| caption      =\n| location     = [[Quebec City]], [[Quebec]], Canada\n| years_active = 1968\u2013present\n| founders     =\n| dates        = July 8th to July 18th (2021) \n| genre        = [[Pop music]], [[folk music]], [[rock music]], [[electronic dance music]], [[Punk rock|punk]], [[hip hop music|hip hop]], [[classical music]], [[:Category:Francophone music|francophone music]], [[world music]]\n| attendance   = 1,800,000 (2017, 11 days total)<ref name=\"lesoleil1\">[https://www.lesoleil.com/affaires/achalandage-record-en-2017-au-feq-db8d0530792bfd2923c1041a75a207ea \"Achalandage record en 2017 au FEQ\"], ''Le Soleil'', Quebec City, February 21th 2018.</ref>\n1,700,000 (2008, 11 days total)<ref name=\"feq1\">[https://www.feq.ca/FEQ/Historique \"Historique du FEQ\"], ''Festival d'\u00e9t\u00e9 de Qu\u00e9bec (Official website)''</ref>\n350,000 (1979, 6 days total)<ref name=\"feq1\" />\n| website      = {{URL|https://www.feq.ca/en/}}\n| capacity = 125,000 (Standard) 3,000 (Gold) 2,000 (Silver) 2,000 (Signature).}}\n\n'''Festival d'\u00e9t\u00e9 de Qu\u00e9bec''' (FEQ) is the biggest outdoor musical event in [[Canada]]. Held since 1968 in [[Qu\u00e9bec City]], the 11-day festival takes place every year in July. FEQ's eclectic programming includes the biggest international stars and emerging artists from around the globe. Its main stage is the biggest self-supporting stage in North America. Festival d\u2019\u00e9t\u00e9 de Qu\u00e9bec is presented by Bell in collaboration with Coors Light. The 53rd edition of the FEQ will take place from July 8 to 18, 2021.\n\n==History==\nThe festival has been taking place annually since 1968. First editions were organized by a group of businesspersons and artists of [[Quebec City]] in order to show the artistic, economic, and tourist potential of the [[Qu\u00e9bec|region]]. During the 1970s and 1980s, the festival specialized in musicians from the [[Francophonie]] and world music.\n\nThe festival grew substantially during the last decade after its decision to diversify its music offering and go after international headliners from genres across the board, including [[rock music]], [[Punk rock|punk]], [[hip-hop]], [[classical music]], [[world music]] and [[Electronic Dance Music|electronic music]].\n\nThe festival reached the million spectators mark for the first time in 2007 and sold-out passes for the first time in 2010.\n\n==Setting==\n[[File:FEQ_Global.jpg|thumb|upright=1.75|The Bell Stage]]\n\nThe outdoor venues :\n* The Bell Stage on the [[Plains of Abraham]] (Capacity 80,000)\n* Parc Grande All\u00e9e (Capacity 25,000; two stages in alternation with no waiting time between sets)<ref>[https://www.feq.ca/media/e6bd1937-0e51-4b6a-bbd4-46c30f857574/NtRVCQ/Feq/M%C3%A9dia/Communiqu%C3%A9s/Communiqu%C3%A9_ParcGA.pdf?download=false \"Cr\u00e9ation du parc Grande All\u00e9e au FEQ\"], ''Festival d'\u00e9t\u00e9 de Qu\u00e9bec (Press Release)'', Quebec City, February 12th 2020.</ref>\n** The Loto-Quebec Stage at Place George-V ( South Side )\n** The SiriusXM Stage at Parc de la Francophonie ( North Side )\n* The Hydro-Quebec Stage at [[Place D'Youville (Quebec)|Place d'Youville]] (Capacity 10,000)\n* The Bell Fibe Stage at Place de L'Assembl\u00e9e-Nationale (Capacity 2,000)\n<br>\nThe indoor venue :\n* Manege Militaire (for all Extra-FEQ concerts starting around midnight)\n<br>\nA site called the \"Place de la famille\" (Family Place) hosts animation and events for children.<br>\n[[Street performer]]s are a staple of the FEQ. They can be found all over the winding streets of [[Old Quebec]] during the festival.\n\n==Main bands (2011\u2013present)==\n* 2011: [[Elton John]], [[Metallica]], [[Avenged Sevenfold]], [[The Black Keys]], [[Dropkick Murphys]], [[John Fogerty]], [[Ben Harper]], [[Simple Plan]], [[Hollywood Undead]].\n* 2012: [[Bon Jovi]], [[Aerosmith]], [[Lionel Richie]], [[LMFAO (group)|LMFAO]], [[The Offspring]], [[Our Lady Peace]], [[Sarah McLachlan]], [[Skrillex]], [[Metric (band)|Metric]], [[Mastodon (band)|Mastodon]], [[City and Colour]].\n* 2013: [[Def Leppard]], [[Guns N' Roses]], [[Bruno Mars]], [[Wu-Tang Clan]], [[Weezer]], [[Rush (band)|Rush]], [[Stevie Wonder]], [[Foreigner (band)|Foreigner]], [[The Black Keys]], [[Ti\u00ebsto]], [[Ellie Goulding]].\n* 2014: [[Lady Gaga]], [[Billy Joel]], [[Journey (band)|Journey]], [[Bryan Adams]], [[The Killers]], [[Soundgarden]], [[Snoop Dogg]], [[Queens Of The Stone Age]], [[Deadmau5]], [[Cypress Hill]].\n* 2015: [[The Rolling Stones]], [[Foo Fighters]], [[Boston (band)|Boston]], [[Megadeth]], [[Keith Urban]], [[Deep Purple]], [[Doobie Brothers|The Doobie Brothers]], [[Jack \u00dc]], [[Iggy Azalea]], [[Milky Chance]].\n* 2016: [[Rammstein]], [[Sting (musician)|Sting]], [[Peter Gabriel]], [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]], [[Duran Duran]], [[Selena Gomez]], [[Ice Cube]], [[Brad Paisley]], [[The Lumineers]], [[The Cult]].\n* 2017: [[Muse (band)|Muse]], [[The Who]], [[Metallica]], [[Pink (singer)|P!nk]], [[Gorillaz]], [[Kendrick Lamar]], [[Backstreet Boys|The Backstreet Boys]], [[Lady Antebellum]], [[Flume (musician)|Flume]], [[Melissa Etheridge]], [[Migos]], [[DNCE]].\n* 2018: [[Foo Fighters]], [[The Weeknd]], [[Neil Young]], [[Shawn Mendes]], [[Beck]], [[Lorde]], [[Future (rapper)|Future]], [[Dave Matthews Band]], [[The Chainsmokers]], [[Jethro Tull (band)|Jethro Tull]], [[Sum 41]].\n* 2019: [[Twenty One Pilots]], [[Mariah Carey]], [[Slipknot (band)|Slipknot]], [[Imagine Dragons]], [[Blink-182]], [[Lynyrd Skynyrd]], [[Kygo]], [[Logic (musician)|Logic]], [[Alt-J]], [[Corey Hart (singer)|Corey Hart]], [[The Offspring]], [[Live (band)|Live]].\n* 2020: Cancelled due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|Covid-19 pandemic]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Festival d'\u00e9t\u00e9 de Qu\u00e9bec}}\n* [https://www.feq.ca/en/ Main site]\n{{Historic rock festival}}\n{{Rock festival}}\n{{coord|46.8017|N|71.2211|W|source:wikidata-and-enwiki-cat-tree_region:CA|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Festival d'ete de Quebec}}\n[[Category:Rock festivals in Canada]]\n[[Category:Folk festivals in Canada]]\n[[Category:Classical music festivals in Canada]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Quebec City]]\n[[Category:Music festivals in Quebec City]]\n[[Category:Recurring events established in 1968]]\n[[Category:Summer festivals]]\n[[Category:1968 establishments in Quebec]]\n[[Category:Music festivals established in 1968]]\n", "name_user": "134.41.172.231", "label": "vandal", "comment": "(Added content.)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Festival_d%27%C3%A9t%C3%A9_de_Qu%C3%A9bec"}
